{
  "text": "The uncertainty associated with some of the validation statistics are computed using the bootstrapping technique [CITATION_1] which involves re-sampling of the data. We construct 10,000 re-samples with replacement onto which bootstrapping is applied at a 95 per cent confidence level. The 50 th percentile is presented as the validation statistic and the 2.5 and 97.5 percentile as the 95 per cent confidence interval.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "198120286"
  },
